      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Then—"
      },
      {
        "type": "equation",
        "latex": "\\frac{dy}{dx} = -4 \\frac{d}{dx} \\log a^{2} + \\frac{d}{dx} \\left( a^{2} \\right) + \\cdots.",
        "description": "Derivative of the expression."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Example 17—Find the value of 4 \\frac{d}{dx} \\left( 3 \\log a \\right) when a = 1, and 4 = 1 - 3 \\log 1."
      },
      {
        "type": "equation",
        "latex": "= 4 \\cdot 0 = 0.",
        "description": "Result of the differentiation."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Hence"
      },
      {
        "type": "equation",
        "latex": "\\frac{d}{dx} \\left( 3 \\log 1 - 3 \\log 3 \\right) = - 3 \\cdot 1 + 0.",
        "description": "Simplified derivative expression."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Note carefully that this result cannot be simplified by combining 1 - 3 \\log \\left( a^{6} \\right) and writing the result as 5 \\cdot 4, which is quite incorrect. The 4 is not raised to the power of 3."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Example 18—Find the value of 3 \\left( 3a^{6} \\right)."
      },
      {
        "type": "equation",
        "latex": "a = 3 - 6 \\cdot 3 \\left( 6 \\right) = 280g.",
        "description": "Expression using differentiation."
      },
      {
        "type": "equation",
        "latex": "\\frac{d}{da} \\left( 3a^{6} \\right) = \\frac{d}{da} \\left( 3\\cdot 280g \\cdot a^{6} \\right) = 6\\cdot 3\\cdot 280g \\cdot a^{5}.",
        "description": "Differentiating the expression."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Thus"
      },
      {
        "type": "equation",
        "latex": "= 1.08g \\cdot 3 \\cdot 280\\cdot a^{6} = 1.08g \\cdot 3 \\cdot 280 + 3.08a = 3.643g6.",
        "description": "Final result of the differentiation."
      }
